Path: godot/tutorials/io/runtime_file_loading_and_saving.rst
Summary: This section explains how to use the FileAccess class in Godot to read and write plain text and binary files.

FileAccess provides methods to access files on the filesystem for reading and writing.

GDScript:
```gdscript
func save_file(content):
    var file = FileAccess.open("/path/to/file.txt", FileAccess.WRITE)
    file.store_string(content)

func load_file():
    var file = FileAccess.open("/path/to/file.txt", FileAccess.READ)
    var content = file.get_as_text()
    return content
```

C#:
```csharp
private void SaveFile(string content)
{
    using var file = FileAccess.Open("/Path/To/File.txt", FileAccess.ModeFlags.Write);
    file.StoreString(content);
}

private string LoadFile()
{
    using var file = FileAccess.Open("/Path/To/File.txt", FileAccess.ModeFlags.Read);
    string content = file.GetAsText();
    return content;
}
```

To handle custom binary formats, FileAccess provides methods to read/write integers, floats, strings, and more. These methods start with "get_" and "store_".

For more control over reading binary files or streams not part of a file, PackedByteArray offers helper methods to decode/encode bytes to integers, floats, strings, and more. These methods start with "decode_" and "encode_". Refer to the binary serialization API for more details.
