Summary: This section details how to load and save image files at runtime in Godot using the Image class.

The Image.load_from_file static method handles loading images from disk, automatically detecting the format based on the file extension. For more control or error handling, specific methods are available for various image formats like JPG, PNG, SVG, TGA, WEBP, and EXR. These include `load_jpg_from_buffer`, `load_png_from_buffer`, `load_svg_from_buffer`, `load_svg_from_string`, `load_tga_from_buffer`, `load_webp_from_buffer`, and `load_exr_from_buffer`.

Godot also provides methods to save images at runtime. These include `save_png`, `save_png_to_buffer`, `save_webp`, `save_webp_to_buffer`, `save_jpg`, `save_jpg_to_buffer`, `save_exr`, and `save_exr_to_buffer`. Methods with the `to_buffer` suffix save the image data to a PackedByteArray, which is useful for network transmission or archiving without writing to the filesystem, potentially improving performance by reducing I/O.

Note: If displaying a loaded image on a 3D surface, it's recommended to call Image.generate_mipmaps to prevent the texture from appearing grainy at a distance. This method is also beneficial in 2D for reducing aliasing when downsampling.

GDScript:
# Load an image of any format supported by Godot from the filesystem.
var image = Image.load_from_file(path)
# Optionally, generate mipmaps if displaying the texture on a 3D surface
# so that the texture doesn't look grainy when viewed at a distance.
#image.generate_mipmaps()
$TextureRect.texture = ImageTexture.create_from_image(image)

# Save the loaded Image to a PNG image.
image.save_png("/path/to/file.png")

# Save the converted ImageTexture to a PNG image.
$TextureRect.texture.get_image().save_png("/path/to/file.png")

C#:
// Load an image of any format supported by Godot from the filesystem.
var image = Image.LoadFromFile(path);
// Optionally, generate mipmaps if displaying the texture on a 3D surface
// so that the texture doesn't look grainy when viewed at a distance.
// image.GenerateMipmaps();
GetNode<TextureRect>("TextureRect").Texture = ImageTexture.CreateFromImage(image);

// Save the loaded Image to a PNG image.
image.SavePng("/Path/To/File.png");

// Save the converted ImageTexture to a PNG image.
GetNode<TextureRect>("TextureRect").Texture.GetImage().SavePng("/Path/To/File.png");
